TLDR of what happened:

I had a working rootless Podman GitLab Runner running through systemctl --user / Quadlet, and Molecule testing was working across ubi7, ubi8, ubi9, and ubi10.

I started adding a global AeroLIT Molecule fixture setup so all role tests could access shared runner-side paths like:

/home/e424770/.local/share/aerolit-molecule

That fixture area contains things like:

* hubs/current
* files/current
* repos/current

The goal was for the CI job container to see those paths, and eventually for Molecule-created test containers to mount/use them too.

The first issue I hit was a simple config.toml syntax issue in the runner Docker volume list. I added the fixture volume but missed a comma, so GitLab Runner failed to parse config.toml. That was fixed by correcting the TOML volume array.

Then the bigger issue started: the GitLab Runner service container itself stopped starting. It was failing before any Molecule job logic even ran.

The first real error was around /home/gitlab-runner:

crun: mkdir /home/gitlab-runner: permission denied

After testing manually, I found the GitLab Runner image declares /home/gitlab-runner as an image volume. Rootless Podman was trying to process/copy-up that image-defined volume and failing in this VDI/rootless Podman environment.

The fix for that first container-start issue was adding this to the Quadlet file:

PodmanArgs=--image-volume=ignore

That got Podman past the image-defined volume problem.

Then the error changed to:

error=chdir /home/gitlab-runner: permission denied

So Podman could now start the container far enough for GitLab Runner to launch, but GitLab Runner itself was trying to use /home/gitlab-runner as its working directory and could not access it.

I tried mounting a writable /home/gitlab-runner directory from my home path, including testing :Z and :U, but that still failed due to rootless Podman/user namespace permission issues.

The final working fix was to avoid /home/gitlab-runner entirely by overriding the GitLab Runner command in the Quadlet file:

Exec=run --user=gitlab-runner --working-directory=/tmp --config /etc/gitlab-runner/config.toml

So the key working Quadlet changes were:

PodmanArgs=--image-volume=ignore

and

Exec=run --user=gitlab-runner --working-directory=/tmp --config /etc/gitlab-runner/config.toml

After that, the GitLab Runner service started successfully, picked up jobs again, and the Molecule pipeline got past the runner startup problem.

The fixture path also appears to be reaching the job container correctly. The job printed:

