You’re seeing a user-namespace bind-mount permissions problem.

Even though you did:

chmod 777 "$HOME/.local/share/gitlab-runner/home"

the container’s gitlab-runner user is not the same as your host user. In rootless Podman, container users are mapped through subordinate UID/GID ranges. So “777 should work” feels logical, but rootless user namespace + bind mounts can still fail depending on how the mount is presented.

Your manual test proved this:

crun: stat /home/gitlab-runner: Permission denied

So the next fix is not more chmod. The next fix is to let Podman shift/chown the bind mount for the container user.

Do this next: test the mount with :U

Stop the runner loop first:

systemctl --user stop gitlab-runner
systemctl --user reset-failed gitlab-runner

Now run this test:

podman run --rm \
  --image-volume=ignore \
  --security-opt label:disable \
  -v "$HOME/.local/share/gitlab-runner/home:/home/gitlab-runner:U" \
  --entrypoint /bin/sh \
  localhost/gitlab-runner-known-good:previous \
  -lc 'id; ls -ld /home /home/gitlab-runner; cd /home/gitlab-runner && pwd'

If that works, run the same test as the gitlab-runner user:

podman run --rm \
  --image-volume=ignore \
  --security-opt label:disable \
  --user gitlab-runner \
  -v "$HOME/.local/share/gitlab-runner/home:/home/gitlab-runner:U" \
  --entrypoint /bin/sh \
  localhost/gitlab-runner-known-good:previous \
  -lc 'id; ls -ld /home /home/gitlab-runner; cd /home/gitlab-runner && pwd'

You want it to print:

/home/gitlab-runner

without permission denied.

If the :U test works

Change this line in your Quadlet:

Volume=%h/.local/share/gitlab-runner/home:/home/gitlab-runner

to:

Volume=%h/.local/share/gitlab-runner/home:/home/gitlab-runner:U

Keep this:

